measure.CatchLine: Eliminates landlord's ability to terminate residential tenancy without cause.
measure.MeasureSummary: Eliminates landlord's ability to terminate residential tenancy without cause. Clarifies damages available to tenant for landlord's unlawful no-cause notice or fraudulent landlord-cause notice.
measure.RelatingToFull: Relating to terminations of residential tenancies without tenant cause; creating new provisions; and amending ORS 90.100, 90.147, 90.220, 90.230, 90.300, 90.323, 90.425, 90.427, 90.429, 90.490, 90.493, 90.510, 90.545, 90.555, 90.675, 100.305, 100.320, 105.115, 105.120 and 105.124 and section 3, chapter 13, Oregon Laws 2020 (first special session).
measure.RelatingTo: Relating to terminations of residential tenancies without tenant cause.
measure.FiscalImpact: May have fiscal impact, but no statement yet issued
measure.RevenueImpact: May have revenue impact, but no statement yet issued

historyActions.ActionText: First reading. Referred to Speaker's desk.
